    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Library catalog in which the entries are arranged in a single alphabetical sequence, regardless of their type, so that authors, titles, and other indexing terms are all alphabetized together alphabetically instead of in separate groupings by type. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>所有資料皆依照單一字母順序排列的圖書館目錄，不管是作者、書名或任何可據以分類的索引詞彙，不依類型區分，一律按照字母順序混合編列。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bibliothekskatalog, in dem die Einträge in einer einzigen alphabetischen Folge verzeichnet sind, ohne Berücksichtigung ihres Typs, so dass Autoren, Titel und andere Indexierungsstichworte zusammenhängend alphabetisch geordnet werden, anstatt sie je nach Typ getrennt zu gruppieren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
